This paper involves the creation of a BLAS library for the Parallella platform, which is a hybrid computing platform. The paper also discusses the use of the Epiphany chip as a co-processor for acceleration. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MS (Mathematical Software), followed by cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SC (Scientific Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
